# 📝 Problem Statement

Profit and Loss is one of the most frequently asked topics in placement aptitude tests.

It helps determine whether a seller earns a profit or incurs a loss after selling a product.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 💡 Important Definitions

## 📌 Cost Price (CP)

The price at which an item is purchased.

Example

You bought a laptop for ₹40,000.

CP = ₹40,000

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## 📌 Selling Price (SP)

The price at which the item is sold.

Example

You sold the laptop for ₹48,000.

SP = ₹48,000

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 💰 Profit

A profit occurs when

```text
SP > CP
```

Formula

```text
Profit = SP − CP
```

### Example

CP = ₹500

SP = ₹650

Profit

= 650 − 500

= ₹150

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📉 Loss

A loss occurs when

```text
CP > SP
```

Formula

```text
Loss = CP − SP
```

### Example

CP = ₹1200

SP = ₹1000

Loss

= 1200 − 1000

= ₹200

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📊 Profit Percentage

Formula

```text
Profit % = (Profit × 100) ÷ CP
```

### Example

CP = ₹800

SP = ₹1000

Profit

= 1000 − 800

= ₹200

Profit %

= (200 × 100) ÷ 800

= 25%

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📊 Loss Percentage

Formula

```text
Loss % = (Loss × 100) ÷ CP
```

### Example

CP = ₹2000

SP = ₹1800

Loss

= 2000 − 1800

= ₹200

Loss %

= (200 × 100) ÷ 2000

= 10%

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

